BofA, Other Banks May Be Penalized Over Loan Servicing, WSJ Says

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-02-17T00:08:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/bofa-other-banks-may-be-penalized-over-loan-servicing-wsj-says.html
  Bank of America Corp .,  JPMorgan
Chase & Co . and  Wells Fargo & Co . are among 11 mortgage-loan
servicers that may face penalties levied by U.S. regulators over
internal controls and staffing levels, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
situation.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
